\title{BCI Factory}
\taxon{forest}
\author{monaduck1069}
\date{2026-03-29}
\meta{institution}{BCI Factory}
\meta{url}{https://bcifactory.io}

\p{Brain-computer interfaces belong in communal space. BCI Factory is a shared research floor at \strong{250 Dore Street, San Francisco} producing open hardware, open data, and open firmware for neural signal acquisition at commodity prices.}

\p{Shitty signal is better than no signal. A $10 BCI with noise is infinitely more useful than a $50k BCI you can't touch.}

\p{For the sheaf-theoretic pipeline mathematics, see [[bci-0001]]. For the portal experience (three rooms, rider protocol, T-55 pipeline), see [[horse-0001]]. For walk-up self-serve readings, see [[bcf-0030]]. For electrode augmentation for extended sessions, see [[bci-0009]].}

